The sensitivity of the turn-off detection of apigenin via Cu NCs was carried out. As displayed in Fig. 3
                        A, the fluorescent intensities of Cu NCs decreased progressively when the apigenin amounts varied from 0 μΜ to 300 μM. The logarithm of relative fluorescence intensities (ln(F0/F)) suggested an excellent linear relationship with apigenin amounts changing from 0.5 to 300 μM, and the linear formula was ln(F0/F) = 0.011[Q] + 0.17 (Fig. 3B). The detection limit (LOD) was obtained as 0.079 μM. Compared with previously existing methods for the sensing of apigenin, this as-prepared fluorescence method via Cu NCs as a sensor displayed a good sensitivity, and both linear range and LOD were better than other methods (Table 1
                        ).
